import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    ages = data['age']
    plt.hist(ages, bins=10, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(ages.mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {ages.mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(ages.median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {ages.median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['age'], data['height'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Age')
    ax.set_ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and height?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    plt.bar(name_counts.index, name_counts.values)
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.set_facecolor('#f5f5f5')
    ax.grid(color='white', linestyle='-', linewidth=2)
    ax.spines['bottom'].set_color('#dddddd')
    ax.spines['top'].set_color('#dddddd')
    ax.spines['right'].set_color('#dddddd')
    ax.spines['left'].set_color('#dddddd')
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', colors='#777777')
    ax.tick_params(axis='y', colors='#777777')
    ax.set_xlabel('Age', fontsize=15, fontweight='black', color='#333F4B')
    ax.set_ylabel('Height', fontsize=15, fontweight='black', color='#333F4B')
    ax.set_title('What is the average age and height in the dataset?', fontsize=18, fontweight='bold', color='#333F4B')
    ax.scatter(data['age'], data['height'], color='#FF5733', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Age: {data['age'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(data['height'].mean(), color='blue', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Height: {data['height'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=12)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
